data.name: nudMaxVelLSV.ToolTip
data.value:
Enter maximum velocity in unit/min to apply to this controled axis.
Entering '0' will set range from 0 to 100% of axis velocity for stick movement
Entering value will set range from 0 to X unit/min of axis velocity for stick movement. Maximum value allowed is the max velocity of the selected axis.

data.name: cbJogStepNotify.ToolTip
data.value:
This sets the controller to vibrate to let you know which jog step setting you selected using the right stick (horizontal movement): 1 buzz: .001 setting - Full left stick and release 2 buzz: .010 setting - 1/2 left stick and release 3 buzz: .100 setting - 1/2 right stick and release 4 buzz: 1.000 setting - Full right stick and relase
Unchecking this still allows selection of jog step setting, but with no vibration to let you know which was selected.

data.name: groupboxJogStep.ToolTip
data.value:
This area is for setting custom jog step size settings which may be selected using the right stick x axis (if assigned as a jog selector)
If you leave the selectors blank, they will default to UCCNC default sizes of .001, .010, .100, or 1.000) You may apply a custom value to any of the positions, ie, if you enter .020 in Jog step 2, it will replace the default .010 value.
Step 1 is the left most stick position selection, Step 4 is right most..

data.name: btnConfigForm.ToolTip
data.value:
This opens configuration to set the button code to 'show' or 'open' the plugin.
Once the number is set by user, you may then create your own button or assign that number to a HotKey in UCCNC to open/show the plugin.

data.name: radioButton9.ToolTip
data.value:
Triggers as Velocity increaser uses the left trigger to act as a 1-2x velocity increaser for the left stick functions and the right trigger to act as a 1-2x velocity increaser for the right stick functions.
When enabled, there is no safety locking out jogging motion from the sticks.

data.name: label22.ToolTip
data.value:
Enter button function numbers for associated button.
The function will be run the instant the button is released.
You should put a 'stop' function if required to stop a movement that was started via the 'on press' action of the button.

data.name: label21.ToolTip
data.value:
Enter button function numbers for associated button.
The function will be run the instant the button is pressed down.
Functions that cause movement will require that the associated 'stop' function is assigned to the button release code.

data.name: groupBox3.ToolTip
data.value:
This area is for verifying the controller is working, and to assign actions to the buttons.
On Press activates the function when button is pushed in
Release Press activates the function as button released.
When assigning buttons to command a jog type move, you must assign a 'stop jog' function to the release press so axis will stop!

data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
When initially testing function of controller, un-check the 'Enable Jog' checkbox . All controller inputs will display on the plugin screen so you can verify function without sending commands to move to UCCNC.
Version 2 and up: The plugin now HIDES to task bar icon, and gives a popup prompt when closing the form, asking if hide insead. If plugin is accidentally closed, it may be re-opened and will find the xbox control without restarting UCCNC
The triggers may be assigned as safety devices, preventing jogging unless held depressed, or may be assigned as a velocity increaser.
The left stick is may be assigned to jog any axes desired. THe right stick may be assigned to jog any axes, but may also have the x-axis of the right stick assigned as a jog-step size selector. In v 2.050 and up, a trigger is now used as a safety lockout for the jog step size selection.
The right stick horizontal movement may be used for selecting the 'step jog' increment (.001, .010, .100, 1.000, or any user selectable values). Moving stick full left and releasing selects .001, moving stick half left and release selects .010, moving stick half right selects .100, and moving full right selects 1.0. It is an option to turn on vibrate feedback which will vibrate once for .001, twice for .010, three times for .100, and 4 times for 1.000. The default sizes may also be customized to any value desired.
The 'sensitivity' of both sticks can be set to a linear, squared, or cubic function. The cubic function allows the most control at low feedrates, while allowing ability to still reach 100% speed. Each stick can be set to allow or prohibit combined axis moves in on the diagonal.
The DPAD and Shoulder buttons are able to be congigured for step jogging any axis, or may be fully customized like other buttons. One press of any of the buttons will move one step at the currently set 'step' amount on the screen jog flyout (when set for step jogging).
The Back, Start, and A, B, X, Y buttons are all assignable. Pull down the menus associated with the buttons to select the button function you want to access. Reference the button list in the 'documentation' folder (access by pressing the button). You may set functions to fire either when button initially presses, or when released. Implementing jogging requires an 'activate jog' on press, and a 'stop jog' on release.
The Default feedrate box is a value from 1 to 100, representing percentage of jog feedrate to default back to after relase of the sticks from jogging manually.
Version 2 and up other additions: Adjustable deadbands for both sticks, seperately enable/disable each stick, set maximum velocity in actual units/minute for each stick, Plugin hides to taskbar and double-clicking task icon enables/disables controller. All stick velocity actions re-written to utilize the UC API.
